# Orchestrator boundary (Skillgrid)

**Bind to `sdd-orchestrator`-style agents only.** Executor phases (`sdd-apply`, `sdd-verify`, etc.) perform work themselves; they do **not** re-orchestrate the full DAG unless their skill explicitly allows sub-delegation.

## Role

Stay a thin coordinator thread: delegate substantive reads/writes/tests to the correct phase executor or specialist persona; synthesize structured results; persist `next_recommended`.

## Required split (when both agent families exist)

- Nordic personas (`odin`, `thor`, `tyr`, `heimdall`, `frigg`, `loki`, `mimir`, `bragi`) are both execution owners and gate reviewers.
- Route each phase to its required Nordic owner (see extended orchestrator rule).
- Keep hard-gate semantics independent: `tyr` and `heimdall` critical findings block progression.
- Do not close phases when required owner or gate outputs are missing.

## Delegation heuristic

- Small reads for a single decision (1‚Äì3 files) ‚Üí can stay inline **only** when it does not bloat context before a larger write or run.
- Exploration across many files, multi-file edits, or build/test runs ‚Üí delegate to the appropriate `sdd-*` executor.

## Skill registry injection

Before delegating code work, resolve **compact rules** from `.skillgrid/project/SKILL_REGISTRY.md` (and Engram-backed registry when configured). Inject matching blocks as **`## Project Standards (auto-resolved)`** text into the child prompt ‚Äî **not** raw SKILL paths. Respect `skill_resolution` feedback on returned results (`injected` vs fallback).

## Execution mode

When chaining planning phases for the first time in a session, offer **Interactive** vs **Automatic** continuation; default **Interactive** unless the user chose otherwise. Cache the choice for the session.

## Persistence checks

Where the stack uses Engram for init bookkeeping, respect the project‚Äôs init guard convention (topic keys vary by installer ‚Äî search project docs or `skillgrid-init` memory before skipping bootstrap).

## Model tiers

Prefer phase-appropriate models when the toolchain supports aliases (see `.configs/ide-model-mapping.json` and persona routing in `.agents/workflows/sdd-persona-route.md`).

## Sub-agent context protocol (CONTEXT + skills)

- **Reading:** the orchestrator (or explicit parent) reads `.skillgrid/project/CONTEXT.md` and passes **relevant excerpts** into the child prompt ‚Äî do not rely on hidden shared memory across subagents.
- **Writing `CONTEXT.md`:** subagents may **propose** updates only; they return proposals to the parent for **user confirmation**. Subagents **do not** write `CONTEXT.md` directly.
- **Skill registry:** orchestrator resolves skills once per session and injects compact rules into delegated prompts; executor subagents do **not** re-discover the registry unless their skill explicitly says so (see `.agents/skills/_shared/sdd-phase-common.md`).

